rcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:680,&quot;width&quot;:1022,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:325454,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb5f37920-8dbc-41eb-93ca-9132e1536e3c_1022x680.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb5f37920-8dbc-41eb-93ca-9132e1536e3c_1022x680.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb5f37920-8dbc-41eb-93ca-9132e1536e3c_1022x680.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb5f37920-8dbc-41eb-93ca-9132e1536e3c_1022x680.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://unsplash.com/@jediahowen?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Jed Owen</a>的照片在<a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/bread-on-white-ceramic-plate-beside-sliced-bread-on-table-q6Y8Xr3SoQA?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a>上</figcaption></figure></div><p>目前的大量经济辩论是为什么消费者情绪仍然很低。尽管负面的叙述（“共鸣”）可能会<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/vibes-vs-data">发挥作用</a>，但诸如通货膨胀之类的经济数字肯定很重要。在本周<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-bff">的综述</a>中，我标记了<a href="https://www.briefingbook.info/p/digesting-inflation">一些证据</a>表明，即使暂时的通货膨胀率已经结束，人们也需要一段时间才能克服高通货膨胀的负面心理影响。如果价格回落到以前的水平，似乎可能会帮助人们更快地感觉好起来。</p><p>对于某些产品来说，这种情况确实会发生。自 2022 年中期以来，汽油价格已下跌三分之一以上，按美元计算低于十年前： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ff08f9b-bf72-4d17-abec-06dd8a48788a_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ff08f9b-bf72-4d17-abec-06dd8a48788a_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ff08f9b-bf72-4d17-abec-06dd8a48788a_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ff08f9b-bf72-4d17-abec-06dd8a48788a_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ff08f9b-bf72-4d17-abec-06dd8a48788a_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7ff08f9b-bf72-4d17-abec-06dd8a48788a_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7ff08